result.name: Tian shan xiao guan

reviews.text: Amazing food! Absolutely loved everything! They have pictures and an English menu. Also staff speaks English :) Will come back!

This place has delectable taste, warm atmosphere, and friendly staff. The flavors, the richness of the sauces, and the ingredients all exceeded our expectations. Will become part of our regular routine!

If lamb is your kind of meat, this is an excellent choice. Great tasting XinJiang food.
The lamb casserole with bread is enough for 3, the boss said that we will need 3 dishes, but we ended up not being able to finish the food.
The food was not cheap, on the pricey end.

Delicious authentic Xinjiang cuisine. The restaurant is small but comfortably. The female manager was very friendly and explained clearly about the spiciness of the food. Lamb rib in hand is smooth and tender and very delicious. Similar are the chicken and potatoes with noodle, and barbeque mutton. The spice is not very strong and does not obscure the natural flavour of the mutton. Price is friendly as well.  A nice experience and I will definitely try again.

Wonderful food! Come only if you eat lamb, or else this place is not for you. The herbs and lamb balance is right. Unlike most lamb in HK, their lamb do taste and smell like lamb instead of plain red meat...

result.name: 天山小館

reviews.text:
失望極了！
一個人去晚餐，點了手抓羊肉飯和烤羊肉串；
超級不正宗，我真的懷疑廚師是否試吃過新疆菜？
更別提學過作菜了⋯
先說羊肉飯：
飯就是普通飯，淋上煮羊肉排的湯汁，碟子邊上鋪了幾段湯渣的紅蘿蔔，中間擺了幾塊煮湯的羊肉！
羊肉串更加慘烈：
竟然用的是羊腿肉，還是解涷加料直接上火烤，＂堅強＂無比，差點賠上了我最後的幾隻真牙！
香料就不提也罷，但是竟然加了辣油，也就真的太離譜了，讓我強烈懷疑廚師不只沒有去過新疆，沒有跟過師傅，應該也沒有上網搜尋進修⋯甚至可能沒有離開過香港或廣東⋯
Amazing food! Absolutely loved everything! They have pictures and an English menu. Also staff speaks English :) Will come back!

This place has delectable taste, warm atmosphere, and friendly staff. The flavors, the richness of the sauces, and the ingredients all exceeded our expectations. Will become part of our regular routine!

If lamb is your kind of meat, this is an excellent choice. Great tasting XinJiang food.
The lamb casserole with bread is enough for 3, the boss said that we will need 3 dishes, but we ended up not being able to finish the food.
The food was not cheap, on the pricey end.

Delicious authentic Xinjiang cuisine. The restaurant is small but comfortably. The female manager was very friendly and explained clearly about the spiciness of the food. Lamb rib in hand is smooth and tender and very delicious. Similar are the chicken and potatoes with noodle, and barbeque mutton. The spice is not very strong and does not obscure the natural flavour of the mutton. Price is friendly as well.  A nice experience and I will definitely try again.
